JOHANNESBURG - The rand slipped back above the R13 mark against the US dollar on Monday morning as markets await the outcome of the ANC elective conference.
	
	The small tumble followed the delay in the start of voting for the ANC’s top six positions last night. LIVE BLOG: ANC delegates vote for new leader By mid-morning the currency had steadied against major currencies, giving up its earlier gains. It’s currently hovering around R13.10 against the US dollar, R15.44 to the British pound and R17.52 against the Euro. eNCA